<title>THAILAND: Samart Corp taps 8.95 bln yen loan.</title>
<headline>Samart Corp taps 8.95 bln yen loan.</headline>
<dateline>BANGKOK 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Samart Corp Plc said on Friday it would tap a 8.95 billion yen, three-year syndicated loan to raise funds for debt refinancing and for use as operating capital.</p>
<p>Telecommunications firm Samart said in a filing to the Stock Exchange of Thailand the unsecured loan, carrying interest of 90 basis points over the London Interbank Offered Rate, was arranged by Credit Lyonnais Singapore branch.</p>
<p>It gave no further details.</p>
<p>-- Bangkok newsroom (662) 6520642</p>
